== Test plan

Iter 4 sweeps four (presc, sshift, dlyb) operating points to
characterize the SCLK timing margin of the reverted fabric-register
+ unregistered SB_IO pad path. Each block is a fully self-contained
test_serv submission: it programs the bitstream, resets the MP135,
flashes firmware, opens UART, sets the operating point with `p`,
runs `I 1073741824` (1 GiB ping-pong integrity), and closes UART.

The blocks are ordered safest-first per AGENTS.md regression
discipline -- run_md aborts on first failing block, so block D
(presc=4, SCLK=131 MHz, comfortable timing margin) MUST come first
to gate the mission, with blocks B/C/A characterizing what works at
presc=3 (SCLK=164 MHz, marginal). Block D's check is assertable
(`firsterr==-1 AND mbps > 400`); blocks B/C/A always pass after
recording the result so the regression continues to characterize
the full sweep when D succeeds.

The four operating points are:
- D: presc=4 sshift=0 dlyb=0 (SCLK 131 MHz, mission gate, safest)
- B: presc=3 sshift=1 dlyb=0 (SCLK 164 MHz, late-sample at master)
- C: presc=3 sshift=0 dlyb=1 unit=64 (SCLK 164 MHz, DLYB tap mid-range)
- A: presc=3 sshift=0 dlyb=0 (SCLK 164 MHz, iter-2 baseline reproducer)

